dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile represents areas of aggregated socioeconomic and demographic information at the NUTS 3 level for Europe. NUTS 3 units have an average population between 150,000 and 800,000 people. NUTS (Nomenclature des Unit√©s Territoriales Statistiques) refers to the Nomenclature of Territorial Units for Statistics. This layer is part of the 2014 ESRI Data and Maps collection for ArcGIS 10.2. Europe NUTS 3 Demographics provides NUTS 3 level demographic information for Europe. Michael Bauer Research GmbH and ESRI. (2014). Europe NUTS 3 Demographics, 2009-2014. ESRI. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/db078cg9206 For more information: http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/introduction.
